info:

version 2 created on 2020-08-27

building upon the previous erson there is a 4th usb port incorperating the usb2514 (1 to 4)

the hub will allow devices to connect to a computer using usb 2.0

a suitable chip with great documentation (usb8041) has been found for a version with usb 3.0 compatability.

possible future version may look at usb c ports with varying fuctionality

mcp23008 8 port expander ahs been used to hand the IO of buttons and usb port enabling and possible future version if needed can use mcp23017 16 port expander

board maintains the 100*75mm form factor with added 3mm mounting holes
